{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"dd4e8611-a40f-42ea-8687-1420c6b17a1a","content":"No repo files to inspect — this is a general guidance question. Here's how to migrate:\n\n### 1. Replace `VSTest@3` with `DotNetCoreCLI@2` (or a plain `dotnet test` script)\n\nMicrosoft.Testing.Platform doesn't use `vstest.console`; tests run via `dotnet test` (or directly as executables). Drop `VSTest@3` and use:\n\n```yaml\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >\n      --configuration Release\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=TestResults.trx\"\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n```\n\nOr equivalently, a script step:\n\n```yaml\n- script: >\n    dotnet test **/*Tests.csproj\n    --configuration Release\n    --logger \"trx;LogFileName=TestResults.trx\"\n    --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n    --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n```\n\n### 2. Publish TRX results\n\n```yaml\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish test results'\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n  condition: succeededOrFailed()\n```\n\n### 3. Publish code coverage\n\n```yaml\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish code coverage'\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n  condition: succeededOrFailed()\n```\n\n> If you're using the default Microsoft collector, the output is `.coverage` format. For Cobertura XML (needed by `PublishCodeCoverageResults@2`), switch to **coverlet**: `--collect \"XPlat Code Coverage\"` and add the `coverlet.collector` NuGet package.\n\n### 4. Project-side changes\n\nIn each test `.csproj`, opt in to the new platform:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n### Key differences from `VSTest@3`\n\n| Concern | Old (VSTest@3) | New (dotnet test) |\n|---|---|---|\n| Runner | vstest.console | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n| TRX reports | Built-in | `--logger trx` (same) |\n| Code coverage | `codeCoverageEnabled: true` | `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` or coverlet |\n| Task | `VSTest@3` | `DotNetCoreCLI@2` or `script` |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1916fd27-e1f9-43ae-b519-35386b6a0ee8","outputTokens":701,"requestId":"4818:136CC7:2FC45C9:345C268:69FBE2A9"},"id":"d81368b9-53ea-4a3c-9a8a-2c9c7b65b312","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:54:17.303Z","parentId":"02bcf2e1-8ff1-4f5b-a098-294bfbc1add3"}
